- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the use of rigorous mathematical techniques for correctness in the development of high performance algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper focuses on the derivation of algorithms for dense linear algebra libraries for distributed memory parallel computers. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the implementation of numerical algorithms for dense linear algebra libraries. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the practical application of the goal-oriented approach to software development in the context of dense linear algebra libraries. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper may touch on programming language issues related to the implementation of the derived algorithms.
